cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.RO, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the development of a reference architecture for the design of CPPS, which involves software engineering principles. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the cognitive abilities of CPPS, which involves the usage of AI techniques such as machine learning. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as CPPS involves the integration of physical and computational resources, which requires control and monitoring of the system. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is relevant as CPPS can involve the usage of robots in production systems. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also relevant as the paper discusses the usage of data and sensors to enable cognition in CPPS, which involves machine learning techniques.
